HEADWORD: Gade
<hw>Gade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Cod the fish.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small British fish (<spn>Motella
argenteola</spn>) of the Cod family.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A pike, so
called at Moray Firth; -- called also <altname>gead</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
